  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "A simple caching module that has `set`, `get` and `delete` methods and works a little bit like memcached.\nKeys can have a timeout (`ttl`) after which they expire and are deleted from the cache.\nAll keys are stored in a single object so the practical limit is at around 1m keys.",
